New MVNO Noble Mobile launches with former presidential candidate Andrew Yang as CEO, offering cash back rewards to clients using less than 20 GB of monthly (Monica Alleven/Fierce Network)
YouTube plans to expand its likeness detection tech to all Partner Program creators in the next months; creators can opt in by uploading an image of their face (Kerry Flynn/Axios)
YouTube unveils new livestreaming features, including letting creators transition between public and members-only streams, and ads that run next to the stream (Lauren Forristal/TechCrunch)
Salesforce launches Missionforce, a new business unit focused on integrating AI into defense workflows concerning personnel, logistics, and decision-making (Rebecca Szkutak/TechCrunch)
YouTube unveils new ways for creators to earn with brand deals and the Shopping program, including letting them swap out brand sponsorships in longform videos (Aisha Malik/TechCrunch)
YouTube says it has paid out $100B+ to creators over the last four years and the number of YouTube channels making over $100K from TV screens has jumped 45% YoY (Zach Vallese/CNBC)
YouTube unveils new generative AI tools for Shorts, including a custom version of Veo 3 called Veo 3 Fast, which includes sound, and an Edit with AI feature (Aisha Malik/TechCrunch)
Disney, Universal, and WBD sue China's MiniMax, alleging that its image- and video-generating service Hailuo AI was built from stolen intellectual property (Reuters)
Humanoid robot startup Figure raised a $1B+ Series C led by Parkway Venture Capital at a post-money valuation of $39B, up from $2.6B in February 2024 (Jackie Davalos/Bloomberg)

HR software provider Workday agrees to acquire Sana, an AI startup specializing in workplace tools, for $1.1B; the transaction is set to close before January 31 (Nicholas G. Miller/Wall Street Journal)
Israel-based Vega, which offers an AI-based security analytics platform, raised $65M in seed and Series A led by Accel at a $400M valuation (Meytal Vaizberg/Globes)
Google launches the Agent Payments Protocol, or AP2, designed to securely facilitate agent-led payments across platforms, with the support of 60+ organizations (Sabrina Ortiz/ZDNET)
OpenAI says it is developing a "different ChatGPT experience" for teens and plans to use age-prediction tech to bar kids under 18 from the standard version (Megan Morrone/Axios)
Sources: Oracle is among a consortium of companies that would enable TikTok to continue its US operations if the US and China finalize their framework deal (Jennifer Jacobs/CBS News)
Tech executives say the Trump administration's stake in Intel and its intervention into other private businesses have had a chilling effect on decision making (Yasmin Khorram/Politico)
